msgctxt "mn151:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 151 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 151 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn151:0.2"
msgid "Piṇḍapātapārisuddhisutta "
msgstr "The Purification of Alms "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn151:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn151:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn151:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Sāriputta came out of retreat and went to the Buddha. He bowed and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him, "

#. REF: nya2, pts-vp-pli3.294, sc2
msgctxt "mn151:2.1"
msgid "“Vippasannāni kho te, sāriputta, indriyāni, parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto. "
msgstr "“Sāriputta, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright. "

#. VAR: bahulaṃ → etarahi bahulaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn151:2.2"
msgid "Katamena kho tvaṃ, sāriputta, vihārena etarahi bahulaṃ viharasī”ti? "
msgstr "What kind of meditation are you usually practicing these days?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn151:2.3"
msgid "“Suññatāvihārena kho ahaṃ, bhante, etarahi bahulaṃ viharāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, these days I usually practice the meditation on emptiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn151:2.4"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, sāriputta. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Sāriputta! "

msgctxt "mn151:2.5"
msgid "Mahāpurisavihārena kira tvaṃ, sāriputta, etarahi bahulaṃ viharasi. "
msgstr "It seems you usually practice the meditation of a great man. "

#. VAR: eso → hesa (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn151:2.6"
msgid "Mahāpurisavihāro eso, sāriputta, yadidaṃ—"
msgstr "For emptiness is the meditation of a great man. "

msgctxt "mn151:2.7"
msgid "suññatā. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn151:3.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, sāriputta, bhikkhu sace ākaṅkheyya: "
msgstr "Now, a mendicant might wish: "

msgctxt "mn151:3.2"
msgid "‘suññatāvihārena bahulaṃ vihareyyan’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "‘May I usually practice the meditation on emptiness.’ So they should reflect: "

msgctxt "mn151:3.3"
msgid "‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, atthi nu kho me tattha cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti? "
msgstr "‘Along the path that I went for alms, or in the place I wandered for alms, or along the path that I returned from alms, was there any desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in my heart for sights known by the eye?’ "

msgctxt "mn151:3.4"
msgid "Sace, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti: "
msgstr "Suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that "

msgctxt "mn151:3.5"
msgid "‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, atthi me tattha cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā tesaṃyeva pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya vāyamitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "there was such desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in their heart, they should make an effort to give up those unskillful qualities. "

msgctxt "mn151:3.6"
msgid "Sace pana, sāriputta, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno evaṃ jānāti: "
msgstr "But suppose that, upon checking, a mendicant knows that "

msgctxt "mn151:3.7"
msgid "‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, natthi me tattha cakkhuviññeyyesu rūpesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti, tena, sāriputta, bhikkhunā teneva pītipāmojjena vihātabbaṃ ahorattānusikkhinā kusalesu dhammesu. "
msgstr "there was no such desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in their heart, they should meditate with rapture and joy, training day and night in skillful qualities. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4-8, pts-vp-pli3.295, sc3
msgctxt "mn151:4-8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, sāriputta, bhikkhunā iti paṭisañcikkhitabbaṃ: "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant should reflect: "

msgctxt "mn151:4-8.2"
msgid "‘yena cāhaṃ maggena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ, yasmiñca padese piṇḍāya acariṃ, yena ca maggena gāmato piṇḍāya paṭikkamiṃ, atthi nu kho me tattha sotaviññeyyesu saddesu … pe … "
msgstr "‘Along the path that I went for alms, or in the place I wandered for alms, or along the path that I returned from alms, was there any desire or greed or hate or delusion or repulsion in my heart for sounds known by the ear … "

msgctxt "mn151:4-8.3"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyesu gandhesu … "
msgstr "smells known by the nose … "

msgctxt "mn151:4-8.4"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyesu rasesu … "
msgstr "tastes known by the tongue … "

msgctxt "mn151:4-8.5"
msgid "kāyaviññeyyesu phoṭṭhabbesu … "
msgstr "touches known by the body … "

msgctxt "mn151:4-8.6"
msgid "manoviññeyyesu dhammesu chando vā rāgo vā doso vā moho vā paṭighaṃ vāpi cetaso’ti? "
msgstr "thoughts known by the mind?’ "

